Both required outputs are written. Summary of what I did:

**Analysis** — Ran 10 iterations on `dataset.parquet` (50,000 prostate cancer patients, outcome `pfs_months`):
1. Main treatment effects → mostly null; small olaparib main effect (p=0.003)
2. Prognostic features → ECOG, mCRPC, albumin, LDH, PSA, weight loss all strongly associated; age direction reversed
3. Biomarker × treatment interactions → **olaparib × BRCA2 strongly supported** (β=+1.62 mo, p=4e-61); Lu177×PSMA-high and pembro×MSI-high NULL
4. AR-V7 interactions with enzalutamide/abiraterone → both null
5. Treatment × mCRPC / Gleason → only docetaxel×mCRPC borderline
6. Inflammation markers → CRP and NLR add nothing after adjustment
7. Comorbidities → all non-significant
8. Demographics / insurance → no disparities detected
9. SNP screen → no SNP survives Bonferroni
10. Full multivariable model (R²=0.95) → confirms ECOG/mCRPC/albumin/LDH/PSA/Gleason/weight loss as adjusted prognostic factors and persistence of the olaparib×BRCA2 predictive interaction

**Outputs**:
- `transcript.json` (10 iterations, 70 hypotheses, 72 analyses; validated against `transcript_schema.json`)
- `analysis_summary.txt` (narrative synthesis)
